data.text:
Kairana, Uttar Pradesh, India

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 29.393990, 77.200272.

Kairana is a large commercial town in the state of Uttar Pradesh, located between the cities of Panipat and Muzaffarnagar. It is a historic settlement with the population close to 80 thousand people, with a very large portion of Muslim population (close to 80 per cent). The town is also famous as a birthplace of a few famous people, including Rahmatullah Kairanawi, a historic Muslim philosopher, and a modern politician, Tabassum Begum.
